    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996.2-generation Carrera is a purist\u2019s specification, powered by a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six mated to a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The M96 engine delivers linear power with a 7,200 RPM redline, benefiting from a proactive IMS bearing inspection and a fresh rear main seal to ensure long-term drivetrain reliability. The chassis maintains its legendary poise, featuring a multi-link rear suspension setup and MacPherson struts that offer exceptional turn-in and communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. Deceleration is handled by four-piston Monobloc fixed calipers over vented rotors, showing minimal swept-area wear. While the exterior displays minor road-going patina, the mechanical fundamentals are robust, making this a high-performance driver\u2019s car optimized for technical canyon roads.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 0
    },
    {
